<emphasis box="[1078,1147,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="94">lynda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a blue tinted dorsal surface, a short meso– and metasterna, and externally descending epipleuron with faint depressions for reception of femoral apices. These characters along with male genitalia will aid in identification.
</paragraph>
